description:
Duniyadari- 26 March Episode

First Headline-

92 soldiers were killed in a terrorist attack by Boko Haram in African Country Chad.

Second Headline-  

Death in United States of America from Coronavirus (COVID-19) exceed 1,000.  US Senate on March 25 passed a $2.2 trillion emergency relief package for novel coronavirus pandemic.

Third Headline-

Death toll from Coronavirus (COVID-19) exceed 7,000 in Italy. Spain has registered more than 4,000 deaths from novel coronavirus.

Badi Khabar-

Latest figures released by China's three wireless carriers show a drop of around 21 million sim cards in past three months. These three companies are China Mobile Limited, China Unicom Hong Kong Limited and China Telecom Corp Limited. A section on social media along with few news websites wonder where these 21 million Chinese cellphone users disappeared in three months. Few suggest, this could be a hint of much more fatalities in China from novel coronavirus COVID-19.
